2.Dynamically typed-  Variable type is decided at runtime, not at compile time
                      Eg-def add(a, b):
                         return a + b
                         print(add(2, 3))        # integers
                         print(add("A", "B"))    # strings
                         print(add([1], [2]))    # lists

