23.Overloading-same method but different parameters in same class.
   Overriding -When a child class redefined a same method from the parent class.We need inheritance for overriding always.Runtime
    Eg-class Animal:
          def sound(self):
              print("Animal makes a sound")
      class Dog(Animal):
          def sound(self):
              print("Dog barks")
      dog = Dog()
      dog.sound()

